text:
Following a double-overtime loss to Washington State at home, all Mark Helfrich heard when he dialed into the Pac-12 Conference's weekly conference call of football coaches was dead air.
The Oregon Ducks coach received zero questions from reporters across the region and country, even as his team faced many.
Fast forward to Tuesday. After a 26-20 win at Washington, which marked UO's 12th consecutive in the series against UW and the return of quarterback Vernon Adams Jr., Helfrich was again a popular coach to talk with.
Topics he discussed included:
— How Oregon's facilities are key to Oregon's recruiting strategy;
— How Adams played against the Huskies, and can improve;
— How Washington's defense has improved despite losing four NFL draft picks;
— What has keyed Utah quarterback Travis Wilson's improvement;
— Whether his coaching strategy has changed despite newfound struggles;
— Does he consider his team a "spoiler" in the Pac-12 race?
— What is Washington State doing better this season?
